Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{})

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and onion and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the garlic and @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in the @boiled water{500%ml} for the risotto, @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and @dried rosemary{2%sachets}.

Stir to combine, bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly crush the @hazelnuts{20%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}. Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

When the risotto has 10 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g}(halved thick stems lengthways) and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water, then cover with a lid (or foil) and allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove the lid, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the heat.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the @butter{20%g} and @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Stir the @baby spinach{40%g} into your risotto a handful at a time and allow to wilt until it's piping hot.

Share the risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the broccoli.

Scatter over the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} and scatter over the hazelnuts. Drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!